Program: Thinking Allowed
Title: Politically connected firms - Gangs and Territory
Link: https://www.bbc.co.uk/programmes/b00w7c91
Last Broadcast Date: Mon 6 Dec 2010
Professor Laurie Taylor explores the connections between politics and business with economist Mara Faccio, who talks about her new research into the subject. Laurie also talks to criminologist Judith Aldridge and discusses her research about how territory influences youth gangs. They are joined by Peter Squires from Brighton University. Producer: Chris Wilson. Show less